The paper deals with privacy risks in cloud storage services and proposes a usable privacy approach to mitigate the problem. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR) and "Human-Computer Interaction" (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing a dataset and conducting a web experiment, which could fall under the categories of "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI) and "Computers and Society" (cs.CY). Finally, the paper also mentions a simulation on top of large collaboration networks, which could relate to the category of "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS).
